To insert a user:

sudo docker compose -f compose.yaml exec db psql -U nestuser -d content_db -c "INSERT INTO users (email, password_hash) VALUES ('admin@circus.com', '123456');"


To view tables: \dt

To query data: SELECT * FROM contents;

To update data: UPDATE contents SET title = 'Novo Titulo' WHERE display_order = 1;

To exit the shell: \q


to insert the characters

docker-compose exec db psql -U nestuser -d content_db
